    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sytle and culture of the Licchavi era,  ca. 450-ca. 750 CE  in Nepal, defined by the rule by the Licchavi dynasty. The dynasty originated in India, used Sanskrit as a court language, issued Indian-style coins, maintained close ties to India, and also had economic and political relations with Tibet.</Note_Text>
